// nodule: std.numerics
// `std.numerics` ‚Äî the honest Œµ/Œ¥ carrier and meet-composition surface (M-512, issue #153).
//
// `std.numerics` is the library home for *carrying a value together with its `Meta`-attached
// `{Bound, GuaranteeStrength}`* ([`Approx<T>`]) and for the **meet-composition /
// refuse-without-a-rule** posture that keeps bounds honest. The verified Œµ/Œ¥ kernels live in
// `mycelium-numerics` (ADR-010); this module is their **ergonomic, never-upgrading surface**
// (KC-3 ‚Äî it adds no trusted bound algebra, it consumes it).
//
// # Honesty crux (C2 / VR-5)
//
// A helper's guarantee tag is exactly what its basis supports and is **never upgraded**: strength
// composes by [`GuaranteeStrength::meet`] (weakest-wins), bounds propagate with **outward
// (directed) rounding** (via `mycelium-numerics`), and an op lacking a sound rule **refuses**
// (`Err`) rather than fabricating a bound. `Proven` is constructible **only** via a
// [`ProvenThm`]-typed witness token ‚Äî there is no other path (FR-N3, type-level; sealed module).
//
// # Design grounding
//
// - Spec: `docs/spec/stdlib/numerics.md` (¬ß3 exported-op surface, ¬ß4 guarantee matrix)
// - ADR-010 (the two bound kernels + shared certificate), ADR-011 (`BoundBasis` universal)
// - `mycelium-numerics` ‚Äî M-201 `::error`, M-202 `::prob`, M-203 `::cert` (Done 2026-06-09)
// - RFC-0016 ¬ß4.1 C1‚ÄìC6, ¬ß4.2 Ring-1, ¬ß4.5 guarantee matrix
// - RFC-0001 ¬ß4.3/¬ß4.7 (`Meta`, guarantee lattice, M-I1‚ÄìM-I4)
// - Task M-512, issue #153
//
// # Œµ-ownership (NFR-N2 ‚Äî RESOLVED)
//
// This module is the Œµ-carrier home, so it now **owns** the `Declared`-strength float Œµ that
// `std.math` previously held locally: [`DECLARED_FLOAT_EPS`]. `std.math` re-exports it from here
// rather than restating it (the math.md ¬ß7-Q2 / README ¬ß5 Œµ-ownership FLAG). The value is a
// **`Declared`** placeholder (`UserDeclared` basis) for the unaudited libm transcendental floor;
// its honest upgrade to a `Proven` magnitude is owned by the kernel (ADR-010 / `mycelium-numerics`)
// and the audited `wild`/FFI floor (M-541), reachable only via a checked basis (VR-5) ‚Äî never by
// restating a tighter number here.
//
// ## Ambient Representation (RFC-0012 ¬ß8-Q3)
//
// This crate's public API participates in the RFC-0012 ambient-representation contract:
// the representation choice (binary/ternary/dense/VSA) is implicit at the call site but
// always reified, queryable, and EXPLAIN-able ‚Äî never a black box (C3/SC-3).
// [Declared per RFC-0012; direction accepted in DN-07 ¬ß8-Q3; per-ring pass scheduled as M-540.]
//
// **For this crate (Ring 2, Tier B):** Numerics ops are representation-agnostic (the bound
// algebra operates over floats and fixed-point values regardless of `Repr`); however, every
// result always carries an explicit `Bound` with its `BoundBasis` ‚Äî no precision is implicitly
// reduced or silently upgraded. The `Proven` strength is reachable only via a `ProvenThm`
// witness token; there is no ambient path to `Proven`.
//
// # Stability (DN-66 freeze, 2026-07-01)
//
// This crate's public API, as documented in `docs/spec/stdlib/numerics.md` (spec status:
// Accepted (2026-06-20)) and asserted by its guarantee-matrix table, is the **frozen baseline** per
// [DN-66](../../../docs/notes/DN-66-Stdlib-Stable-API-Freeze-And-Rust-Crate-Retirement-Status.md).
// A future breaking change here needs a spec amendment + changelog entry, not a silent edit (G2).
//
// **Unfrozen for the gap-closure window (ADR-045, Accepted 2026-07-10):** this DN-66 freeze is
// lifted per [ADR-045](../../../docs/adr/ADR-045-Kernel-And-Lexicon-Unfreeze-For-Early-Gap-Closure.md)
// for a bounded window; a breaking change here still needs a spec amendment + changelog entry
// (G2), not a silent edit ‚Äî the window closes per the ADR-045 ¬ß2.4 re-freeze conditions, bound by
// the DN-99 residual worklist.
// It remains the RFC-0031 D6 differential-oracle reference; no `.myc` port of this module exists yet, so the D6 retirement trigger has not fired and no item here is `#[deprecated]`.
// @summary: best-effort transpilation via mycelium-transpile (M-873). Declared,
// unvalidated ‚Äî no Mycelium parser/typechecker confirms this output; see the
// accompanying .gap.json for every construct this pass could not express.
nodule std.numerics;

// Declared: co-emitted guarantee-lattice type ‚Äî referenced in this file but not declared here and not available via a resolved batch `use` (ORACLE-R1 A2; never silent unknown-type file poison ‚Äî G2/VR-5). Variants use DN-140 `*_kw` renames for the reserved lattice keywords (Exact/Proven/Empirical/Declared).
// Declared: renamed Exact -> Exact_kw (reserved-word collision, DN-140)
// Declared: renamed Proven -> Proven_kw (reserved-word collision, DN-140)
// Declared: renamed Empirical -> Empirical_kw (reserved-word collision, DN-140)
// Declared: renamed Declared -> Declared_kw (reserved-word collision, DN-140)
type GuaranteeStrength = Exact_kw | Proven_kw | Empirical_kw | Declared_kw;

// Structured refusal record for `std.numerics` helpers (C1; RFC-0013; spec ¬ß3 `NumErr`).
//
// Every failure mode is an explicit variant ‚Äî no silent coercion, no fabricated default.
type NumErr = BadEps | BadDelta | NoRule | NormMismatch | Overflow;

impl Show[NumErr] for NumErr {
  fn render(x: NumErr) => Bytes =
    match x { BadEps => "BadEps", BadDelta => "BadDelta", NoRule => "NoRule", NormMismatch => "NormMismatch", Overflow => "Overflow" };
};

fn eq_NumErr(a: NumErr, b: NumErr) => Binary{1} =
  match a { BadEps => match b { BadEps => 0b1, _ => 0b0 }, BadDelta => match b { BadDelta => 0b1, _ => 0b0 }, NoRule => match b { NoRule => 0b1, _ => 0b0 }, NormMismatch => match b { NormMismatch => 0b1, _ => 0b0 }, Overflow => match b { Overflow => 0b1, _ => 0b0 } };

// Structured verdict for the tier-i re-validation checker (spec ¬ß3 `CheckErr`; RFC-0013).
type CheckErr = Rejected(Float, Float) | Malformed;
